2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpavel-durov-arrest-france-what-is-telegram-explained-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Earrest%20in%20August%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20French%20authorities%20detained%20him%20for%20four%20days%20in%20solitary%20confinement%20without%20access%20to%20a%20lawyer%20or%20phone%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20read%20the%20list%20of%20charges%3B%20I%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20these%20crimes%2C%20like%20organized%20crime%2C%20selling%20drugs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20I%20realized%20it's%20serious%20because%20they're%20not%20letting%20me%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20said%20the%20charges%20pertained%20to%20alleged%20criminal%20activity%20by%20some%20users%20on%20Telegram%2C%20the%20messaging%20app%20he%20founded%20that%20now%20has%20about%20a%20billion%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrench%20prosecutors%20charged%20Durov%20in%20late%20August%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelegram-ceo-pavel-durov-charges-questions-free-speech-censorship-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esix%20crimes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bcomplicity%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20distribution%20of%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20material%20and%20drug%20trafficking%2C%20arguing%20that%20he%20allowed%20illegal%20activity%20to%20flourish%20on%20Telegram%20while%20refusing%20to%20cooperate%20with%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20faced%20up%20to%2010%20years%20in%20prison%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20500%2C000%20euros%20if%20convicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelegram%20has%20called%20the%20case%20%26quot%3Babsurd%2C%26quot%3B%20insisting%20Durov%20was%20not%20responsible%20for%20user%20behavior%20on%20a%20platform%20that%20complied%20with%20EU%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20remained%20under%20judicial%20control%2C%20a%20legal%20status%20that%20restricted%20his%20travel.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20leave%20the%20country%20because%20there's%20still%20an%20investigation%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Carlson.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20March%20Durov%20was%20allowed%20to%20visit%20Dubai%2C%20where%20he%20had%20been%20living.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20Politico%20reported%20that%20French%20authorities%20had%20denied%20Durov's%20request%20to%20travel%20to%20the%20US%20for%20%26quot%3Bnegotiations%20with%20investment%20funds.%26quot%3B%20The%20Paris%20prosecutor's%20office%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20the%20trip%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20appear%20imperative%20or%20justified.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian-born%20Durov%2C%20who%20holds%20French%20and%20UAE%20citizenship%2C%20said%20he%20was%20not%20contacted%20by%20authorities%20before%20his%20arrest%2C%20despite%20Telegram's%20Dubai%20office%20being%20located%20in%20the%20same%20building%20as%20the%20French%20consulate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20believed%20his%20detention%20was%20a%20pressure%20tactic%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%2C%20very%20strange%20what%20happened%20because%20it%20could%20have%20been%20resolved%20by%20different%20means.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20said%20Telegram%20complied%20with%20European%20law%20and%20handed%20over%20user%20data%20such%20as%20IP%20addresses%20and%20phone%20numbers%20when%20ordered%20by%20a%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20current%20status%20is%20I'm%20not%20on%20trial%2C%26quot%3B%20Durov%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20investigation%20intended%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20there%20will%20be%20enough%20evidence%20to%20put%20this%20on%20trial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%C3%89lys%C3%A9e%20Palace%20and%20Telegram%20didn't%20immediately%20reply%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelegram-pavel-durov-travel-restrictions-france-arrest-charges-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749635909000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68494476f748d8c055f3