%20so%20special%20about%20adlay%20millet%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20adlay%20millet%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20special%20because%20it%20was%20a%20lost%20crop%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20special%20because%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2Fvideo%2Fthey-call-me-queen-of-millets%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eof%20its%20nutritional%20value.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CLike%20most%20millets%2C%20adlay%20also%20has%20a%20very%20low%20glycemic%20index%20(GI)%2C%20making%20it%20a%20good%20alternative%20grain%20l%20for%20people%20with%20diabetes%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Dimum.%20With%20the%20richness%20of%20fibre%2C%20it%20can%20be%20your%20gut%E2%80%99s%20friend.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDimum%20was%20quick%20to%20recognise%20adlay%E2%80%99s%20potential%20as%20a%20healthy%20alternative.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20started%20selling%20it%20as%20a%20grain%2C%20I%20noticed%20quinoa%20was%20its%20closest%20competitor.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20exactly%20like%20rice%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20cooked%20in%20a%20similar%20way%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20makes%20adlay%20a%20worthy%20competitor%20with%20quinoa%20is%20one%2C%20it%20is%20an%20Indian%20variety%20and%20two%2C%20it%20is%20packed%20with%20fibre%20and%20micronutrient%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20best%20part%3F%20It%20is%20incredibly%20versatile!%20%E2%80%9CWe%20now%20have%20chefs%20who%20reach%20out%20to%20me%20and%20are%20keen%20on%20experimenting%20with%20adlay%20to%20make%20Italian%20dishes%20like%20risotto.%20Another%20one%20is%20trying%20to%20replicate%20a%20Mexican%20dish%20with%20this%20millet%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Dimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EReviving%20a%20lost%20crop%20was%20not%20easy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20bringing%20back%20a%20lost%20crop%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20walk%20in%20the%20park%2C%20and%20Dimum%20faced%20her%20share%20of%20hurdles.%20%E2%80%9CSince%20this%20crop%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20grown%20earlier%2C%20we%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20an%20effective%20way%20to%20cultivate%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20of%20the%20crops%20were%20also%20eaten%20by%20some%20wild%20monkeys%20and%20other%20animals.%20Elephants%20had%20also%20attacked%20the%20crops%20in%20the%20past.%E2%80%9D%20Divty%20shares.%20%E2%80%9CWeather%20was%20a%20significant%20complication%20to%20tackle%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dimum%20adds.%20However%2C%20the%20primary%20issue%20came%20during%20the%20harvest%20of%20the%20crop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBecause%20this%20is%20a%20tall%20crop.%20To%20harvest%20the%20tiny%20grains%2C%20you%20need%20to%20use%20both%20hands.%20The%20leaves%20are%20also%20pretty%20sharp%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20use%20bare%20hands%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-06T173005.363-1749211236.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cookies%20and%20bread%20made%20out%20of%20Adlay%20millet%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-06T173005.363-1749211236.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-06T173005.363-1749211236-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-06T173005.363-1749211236-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20http